rComments: He goes through the concept carefully, and follows up with various examples. Out of the four first year MAT professors I've seen, Nikita is the best. He also posts his notes online, so you don't have to worry about failing because you can't read the profs handwriting (as with many MAT135/136 profs).

I usually get really sleepy during math class but Nikita was funny and spoke very clearly! He went over multiple examples from each chapter and even some possible midterm/exam questions. I believe he was the only prof to post online lecture notes, as well as a chart summarizing the things we had to know for the final exam. 10/10.

Out of all the first year math profs, Nikita is the best by far. He explains things clearly and you understand math so well. Plus, he's really funny and his slideshows really help in visualizing the content. Take his class if you want to do well, he cares so much about his students.
